Reasoning: The paper focuses on the analysis of scientific communities and their dynamics, which falls under the scope of social networks and information retrieval. The use of arXiv repository covering a period of 10 years of publications in physics suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the co-authorship and citation behaviors in a community, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The analysis of the dataset at a global, meso, and micro-level suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
